===Proper noun===
'''Ariana'''

# A female [[given name]].  It is both an Italian simplification of the [[Greek]] name [[Ariadne]] ("most  holy"; Cretan Greek ''αρι'' (ari) "most" and ''αδνος'' (adnos) "holy"), and a [[Welsh]] name meaning "silver" (derived from Welsh ''arian'', "silver").
# In middle persian languages, the name Ariana also means, Anyone who's been born in aryan teritories such as Persian empire including Afghnistan and Pakistan and some parts of India.  To date, many call themselves Ariana because of this.

